    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-04-24T03:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-04-24T03:35:00-05:00" n="461"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890H.6363/90: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Merriam</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-04-24T12:00:00+03:25"
                            >April 24, 1937—noon.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 24—11:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. Hart confirms that petroleum concession has been ratified by the Afghan
                        Parliament.<note n="6" xml:id="d461fn6">In telegram No. 74, June 21, 1938, 9
                        p.m., the Chargé in Iran reported to the Department that on June 19, 1938,
                        Mr. Hart had given the Afghan Government written notice of the cancellation
                        of this concession (890H.6363/104).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Merriam</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
